60.1	Mithras	Mithraic mysteries	The Mithraic Mysteries were a mystery religion practised in the Roman Empire from about the 1st to 4th centuries AD. The name of the Persian god Mithra, adapted into Greek as Mithras, was linked to a new and distinctive imagery. Romans also called the religion Mysteries of Mithras or Mysteries of the Persians; modern historians refer to it as Mithraism, or sometimes Roman Mithraism. The mysteries were popular in the Roman military.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/MithraReliefvert.jpg/300px-MithraReliefvert.jpg
